pullRequest.title: project routing implementation
pullRequest.bodyText:
UR Web App Project Routing Implementation.
This PR has many new files but the intention of this PR is to check feature modules and Routing.
Next PR will have codes in some of the files,all code related to a feature or sub-feature

nodes.bodyText: Remove extra "Component" from class name and file name.
enableTracing should be based on whether this is development or not.
empty path usually goes at the end of the routes list.
Better to provide in the ManageAccountModule
I don't think this needs a route prefix. Having everything nested under user doesn't add any value, and lets us use user in the "manage user" module
path: 'account/setup'? Do we have other account routes?
Why add another route? If this module only does one thing than just keep the empty path.
These seem like Participant routes, not Site routes
This whole app is for managing things. Just call it the UserModule.
